ashington%2C%20DC%2C%20apartment%20from%20a%20top%20official%20for%20the%20right-wing%20advocacy%20group%20Americans%20for%20Prosperity%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Colorado%20congresswoman's%20office%20and%20to%20records%20reviewed%20by%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20for%20Prosperity%20is%20a%20key%20part%20of%20the%20conservative%20influence%20network%20originally%20funded%20by%20the%20oil-billionaire%20brothers%20Charles%20and%20David%20Koch.%20After%20David%20Koch's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdavid-koch-dead-at-age-79-report-2019-8%5C%22%3Epassing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20network%20has%20continued%20to%20remain%20active%20in%20conservative%20causes.%20The%20official%2C%20who%20Insider%20is%20not%20naming%20for%20security%20reasons%2C%20has%20been%20a%20senior%20executive%20with%20Koch-linked%20groups%20for%20years.%20He%20owns%20a%20%241.3%20million%20row%20house%20in%20the%20Capitol%20Hill%20neighborhood%20with%20his%20wife%2C%20and%20they%20rent%20out%20the%20lowest%20floor%20as%20a%20one-bedroom%20garden%20apartment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20no%20ethics%20rules%20or%20laws%20that%20bar%20members%20of%20Congress%20from%20renting%20apartments%20from%20people%20affiliated%20with%20lobbying%20groups.%20But%20the%20arrangement%20is%20an%20indicator%20of%20how%20small%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20can%20be%2C%20and%20how%20closely%20entwined%20Washington%20legislators%20can%20become%20with%20the%20people%20who%20are%20paid%20to%20influence%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoebert%20boasts%20on%20her%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fboebert.house.gov%2Fissues%2Foversight-and-accountability%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20she%20came%20to%20Congress%20to%20%26quot%3Bdrain%20the%20swamp%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20blasts%20the%20%26quot%3BWashington%20way%20of%20pandering%20to%20lobbyists%2C%20special-interest%20groups%2C%20and%20partisan%20politics.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20going%20to%20meetings%20with%20lobbyists%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20spending%20time%20in%20the%20District.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20official%20that%20Boebert%20pays%20rent%20to%20is%20not%20a%20registered%20lobbyist%2C%20Americans%20for%20Prosperity%20has%20spent%20more%20than%20%243.9%20million%20lobbying%20Congress%20since%20Boebert%20joined%20the%20House%2C%20according%20to%20congressional%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20gives%20Boebert%20a%20100%25%20career%20rating.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20does%20differ%20from%20Americans%20for%20Prosperity%20on%20some%20points%3A%20Boebert%20is%20far%20more%20restrictive%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20immigration%2C%20a%20major%20departure%20from%20the%20Koch-backed%20groups%20that%20have%20previously%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehill.com%2Flatino%2F596677-exclusive-koch-groups-launch-ad-campaign-to-promote-immigration-reform%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20pushed%20for%20legal%20status%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20so-called%20%26quot%3BDreamers.%26quot%3B%20The%20Kochs%20have%20also%20launched%20an%20effort%20to%20deny%20Trump%20the%20GOP%20presidential%20nomination%3B%20Boebert%20supports%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEthics%20experts%20told%20Insider%20that%20Boebert%20is%20not%20violating%20any%20rules%20by%20renting%20from%20someone%20who%20helps%20run%20an%20advocacy%20group%2C%20as%20long%20as%20she%20pays%20the%20market%20rate.%20Anthony%20Fakhoury%2C%20a%20Boebert%20spokesperson%2C%20said%20she%20pays%20%242%2C000%20per%20month%20under%20the%20terms%20of%20her%2012-month%20lease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20going%20rents%20in%20Boebert's%20neighborhood%20vary%20widely.%20According%20to%20Census%20data%2C%20the%202021%20median%20rent%20in%20the%20zip%20code%20was%20%242%2C395%2C%20a%20number%20that%20incorporates%20all%20home%20sizes%20and%20includes%20utilities.%20An%20Insider%20survey%20of%20advertised%20rents%20for%20other%20one-bedroom%20apartments%20nearby%20ranged%20from%20%241%2C695%20to%20just%20under%20%247%2C000%20per%20month%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20location%20and%20amenities%20offered.%20A%20no-longer-active%20listing%20for%20Boebert's%20apartment%2C%20provided%20by%20Fakhoury%2C%20says%20that%20the%20typical%20monthly%20rent%20for%20one-bedroom%20apartments%20nearby%20is%20%243%2C061%20%E2%80%94%20and%20%244%2C000%20for%20%26quot%3Bpremium%26quot%3B%20units.%20Zillow%20estimates%20that%20the%20rent%20for%20Boebert's%20apartment%20would%20be%20%243%2C518.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20unit%20boasts%20stainless%20steel%20appliances%2C%20a%20walk-in%20closet%2C%20granite%20countertops%2C%20and%20in-unit%20washer%20and%20dryer.%20Despite%20being%20a%20basement%20unit%2C%20it%20appears%20to%20get%20lots%20of%20natural%20light.%20Its%20main%20selling%20point%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20close%20proximity%20to%20the%20Capitol.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoebert%20came%20by%20the%20place%20by%20chance%2C%20Fakhoury%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BShe%20found%20a%20flyer%20at%20the%20property%20with%20all%20the%20information%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%20that%20Boebert%20was%20not%20aware%20the%20owners%20were%20connected%20to%20the%20Koch-backed%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20no%20potential%20conflicts%20as%20she%20doesn't%20talk%20policy%20to%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Fakhoury%20said.%20A%20representative%20for%20Americans%20for%20Prosperity%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoebert%20had%20a%20far%20easier%20time%20finding%20a%20home%20in%20Washington%20than%20some%20of%20her%20colleagues.%20Rep.%20Maxwell%20Frost%2C%20a%20Democrat%20from%20Florida%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-congressman-maxwell-frost-denied-apartment-bad-credit-2022-12%5C%22%3Ewas%20rejected%20by%20one%20potential%20landlord%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20bad%20credit.%20%26quot%3BThis%20ain't%20meant%20for%20people%20who%20don't%20already%20have%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20at%20the%20time%20on%20the%20social%20network%20that%20was%20then%20known%20at%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERep.%20Alexandra%20Ocasio-Cortez%20worried%20after%20being%20elected%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falexandria-ocasio-cortez-cant-afford-dc-rent-until-her-salary-starts-2018-11%5C%22%3Ethat%20she%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20a%20place%20in%20the%20district%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F04%2F07%2Fhouse-finalizes-expenses-plan-00090806%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnder%20a%20new%20policy%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3EHouse%20lawmakers%20also%20have%20the%20option%20to%20be%20reimbursed%20for%20some%20rental%20expenses%20provided%20they%20are%20in%20DC%20for%20official%20business.%20Records%20from%20this%20program%20show%20that%20Boebert%20has%20not%20requested%20any%20such%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERenting%20apartments%20from%20people%20affiliated%20with%20lobbying%20groups%20has%20been%20an%20issue%20for%20some%20political%20figures%20in%20the%20past.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2018%2F04%2F27%2Fepa-watchdog-opens-probe-of-scott-pruitts-dc-apartment-rental.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFormer%20EPA%20chief%20Scott%20Pruitt%20was%20investigated%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20renting%20a%20%2450-a-night%20condo%20from%20the%20wife%20of%20the%20head%20of%20a%20lobbying%20firm%20that%20had%20business%20with%20his%20agency.%20Democratic%20Rep.%20Elissa%20Slotkin's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.detroitnews.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fmichigan%2F2022%2F09%2F23%2Felissa-slotkin-leasing-lansing-home-from-business-executive-campaign-donor-niowave%2F69511924007%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econdo%20rental%20from%20a%20campaign%20donor%20and%20businessman%3C%2Fa%3E%20became%20an%20issue%20during%20her%202022%20re-ele