biggest%20challenge%20of%20having%20a%20remote%20team%2C%20Cynthia%20Watson%2C%20the%20executive%20chair%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvirtira.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVirtira%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20remote-work%20consultancy%2C%20told%20Insider%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20working%20across%20four%2C%20five%20time%20zones%2C%20you've%20got%20to%20establish%20a%20core%20working%20area.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAimtal%20requires%20its%20employees%20to%20be%20available%20from%2011%20a.m.%20to%20noon%20and%203%20p.m.%20to%204%20p.m.%20ET.%20Mesh%20said%20these%20time%20frames%20offered%20an%20overlap%20in%20schedules%20that%20made%20communicating%20and%20scheduling%20meetings%20feasible.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20employees%20can%20otherwise%20%26quot%3Bself-manage%26quot%3B%20their%20work%20schedules%2C%20Mesh%20said.%20Aimtal%20devotes%20a%20Slack%20channel%20to%20employee%20availability%20and%20encourages%20them%20to%20post%20when%20they%20are%20and%20aren't%20available.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20important%20to%20me%2C%20and%20for%20everyone%2C%20that%20we%20don't%20have%20this%20always-on%20feeling%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMesh%20often%20works%20at%20night%2C%20when%20she%20feels%20most%20productive%2C%20but%20employees%20know%20they're%20not%20required%20to%20respond%20to%20messages%20from%20her%20outside%20their%20typical%20work%20times.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUse%20asynchronous%20communication%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAsynchronous%20communication%20%E2%80%94%20where%20communication%20isn't%20happening%20in%20real%20time%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20must%20for%20small%20businesses%20with%20remote%20teams%20in%20different%20time%20zones%2C%20Watson%20said.%20It%20ensures%20everyone%20has%20what%20they%20need%20when%20they%20need%20to%20get%20their%20work%20done.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20companies%20can%20post%20meeting%20notes%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-google-drive-guide%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshared%20drive%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20store%20files%20on%20collaboration%20tools%20(such%20as%20Notion%20or%20Confluence)%20that%20everyone%20can%20access%2C%20and%20use%20consistent%20file-naming%20conventions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20want%20to%20make%20it%20easy%20for%20people%20to%20access%20the%20information%20that%20allows%20them%20to%20be%20productive%2C%26quot%3B%20Watson%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22325%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Headshot%20of%20Janet%20Mesh%2C%20CEO%20and%20cofounder%20at%20Aimtal%2C%20in%20a%20white%20long%20sleeve%20shirt%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650855c9cd637c0019c6d8dd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22243%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJanet%20Mesh%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20a%20cofounder%20of%20Aimtal.%3Cp%3EJessie%20Wyman%20Photography%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAimtal%20has%20set%20asynchronous%20communication%20and%20collaboration%20processes%20and%20procedures%2C%20including%20what%20information%20should%20be%20documented%20and%20where%20it%20should%20be%20stored%2C%20Mesh%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20helps%20level%20the%20playing%20field%20and%20keeps%20everyone%20informed%20and%20engaged.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20use%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-slack%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESlack%20channels%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20project-management%20tools%2C%20and%20knowledge-base%20software%20%E2%80%94%20a%20library%20of%20content%20that%20employees%20can%20contribute%20to%20and%20search%20%E2%80%94%20to%20stay%20organized.%20They%20record%20meetings%20and%20presentations%20and%20post%20the%20recordings%20and%20transcripts%20for%20everyone%20to%20access.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26q