rists-1551774035553%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20an%20election%20rally%20in%20Ahmedabad%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EYeh%20hamara%20siddhant%20hai.%20Hum%20ghar%20mey%20ghus%20ke%20maarenge.%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20words%20were%20spoken%20in%20the%20context%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20which%20was%20not%20specified%20by%20name%2C%20and%20where%20the%20LoC%20provides%20legal%20cover%20for%20such%20cross-border%20actions.%20But%20Hindutva%20galleries%20duly%20absorbed%20the%20message%20as%20a%20warning%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20enemies%20everywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20killing%20of%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%2C%20BJP%20constituencies%20%E2%80%93%20which%20believe%20that%20India%20is%20a%20colossus%20on%20the%20global%20stage%2C%20that%20flies%20like%20a%20butterfly%20around%20the%20US%20and%20Europe%20and%20stings%20like%20the%20Mossad%20%E2%80%93%20have%20been%20only%20too%20eager%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cityairnews.com%2Fcontent%2Fradical-sympathisers-mourn-killings-of-khalistan-activists%5C%22%3Econclude%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Indian%20intelligence%20agencies%20were%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDelhi%20has%20denied%20as%20%E2%80%9Cabsurd%E2%80%9D%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20allegation%20that%20%E2%80%9Cagents%20of%20the%20government%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%20had%20a%20role%20in%20the%20murder%20of%20Nijjar%2C%20a%20Khalistani%20activist%2C%20in%20June%20this%20year%20outside%20a%20gurdwara%20in%20the%20British%20Columbian%20city%20of%20Surrey.%20But%20Indian%20social%20media%20warriors%2C%20known%20for%20praising%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cmuscular%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Ctough%E2%80%9D%20policies%2C%20greeted%20the%20news%20of%20his%20killing%20with%20barely%20concealed%20glee%2C%20quickly%20deciding%20that%20under%20a%20muscular%20leadership%20Indian%20intelligence%20agencies%20were%20now%20proactively%20protecting%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20anonymous%20tweeter%20who%20uses%20the%20pseudonym%20The%20Skin%20Doctor%2C%20and%20has%20over%20600%2C000%20followers%20threatened%20Jagmeet%20Singh%2C%20leader%20of%20the%20Canadian%20New%20Democratic%20Party%20with%20the%20same%20fate%20as%20Nijjar%20after%20the%20politician%20vowed%20to%20hold%20Modi%20accountable%20for%20Nijjar%E2%80%99s%20killing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNo%20Jagmeet%2C%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20do%20anything%20to%20the%20Indian%20PM.%20What%20you%20can%20do%3A%20Avoid%20going%20out%20of%20your%20house%2C%20but%20if%20you%20have%20to%2C%20always%20remain%20alert%20and%20aware.%20Increase%20your%20security%2C%20hre%20bodyguard%2C%20bulletproof%20cars.%20Don%E2%80%99t%20let%20them%20meet%20you%20Nijjar%20(sic)%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20the%20Canadian%20allegation%20has%20done%20is%20to%20call%20out%20the%20paradox%3A%20abroad%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20wants%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20%3Cem%3EVishwaguru%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20rules-abiding%20global%20leader%20who%20is%20a%20reliable%20partner%20of%20the%20West%2C%20and%20at%20home%20as%20a%20take-no-prisoners%2C%20tough-talking%20don%2C%20who%20can%20%3Ci%3Eghus%20ke%3C%2Fi%3E%20fix%20all%20perceived%20enemies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20day%20that%20Nijjar%20was%20shot%20dead%2C%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fmajorgauravarya%2Fstatus%2F1670656120166432768%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Etweeter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20uncharacteristic%20restrain%2C%20posted%20a%20short%20message%2C%20that%20code-like%2C%20conveyed%20much.%20%E2%80%9CKhalistanis%20are%20dropping%20like%20flies%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMany%20joined%20the%20dots%20between%20the%20deaths%20of%20three%20Khalistanis%20in%20quick%20succession%20this%20year%20%E2%80%93%20the%20other%20two%20were%20Paramjit%20Singh%20Panjwar%2C%20who%20was%20shot%20dead%20in%20Lahore%3B%20and%20Avtar%20Singh%20Kanda%2C%20who%20died%20in%20a%20Birmingham%20Hospital%20%E2%80%93%20and%20praised%20India%E2%80%99s%20security%20agencies%20for%20taking%20a%20cue%20from%20Mossad%20and%20going%20after%20its%20enemies%20in%20hot%20pursuit.%20A%20WhatsApp%20forward%20helpfully%20compiled%20a%20list%20of%20Khalistanis%20and%20LeT%20jihadists%20who%20had%20been%20taken%20out%20since%202022%2C%20with%20the%20line%2C%20%E2%80%9CSome%20people%20are%20doing%20their%20job.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F21191317%2FUntitled-design-2023-06-21T183517.526.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F21191317%2FUntitled-design-2023-06-21T183517.526.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F21191317%2FUntitled-design-2023-06-21T183517.526-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F21191317%2FUntitled-design-2023-06-21T183517.526-1024x478.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-659441%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar.%20Photo%3A%20Screengrab%20via%20YouTube%2FNews9%20Live%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20web%20portal%2C%20on%20its%20programme%20titled%20%E2%80%98Our%20Men%20In%20Shadows%20Rock%E2%80%99%2C%20interviewed%20a%20retired%20senior%20Army%20officer%20who%20said%20the%20killings%20showed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20dawn%20of%20a%20new%20India%E2%80%9D%20had%20come.%20Another%20online%20portal%20declared%3A%20%E2%80%9CParamjit%20Singh%20Panjwar%20shot%20dead%3A%20Keep%20Calm%20and%20Trust%20the%20Armed%20Forces%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20also%20floated%20the%20theory%20that%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20ISI%20could%20have%20carried%20out%20the%20hits%2C%20as%20these%20men%2C%20purported%20%E2%80%9CPakistan%20ISI%20agents%E2%80%9D%2C%20had%20been%20exposed%20to%20Indian%20security%20agencies%20by%20Amritpal%20Singh%2C%20whose%20Khalistani-style%20movement%20in%20Punjab%20ended%20with%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Famritpal-surrenders-himself-to-punjab-police-to-be-shifted-to-assam-soon%5C%22%3Earrest%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year.%20All%20such%20posts%20concluded%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwhoever%20it%20was%E2%80%9D%2C%20India%20had%20scored%20big%20from%20the%20killings.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEven%20a%20mainstream%20Indian%20weekly%20trod%20similar%20ground.%20It%20blamed%20inter-gang%20warfare%20for%20the%20killing%2C%20but%20could%20not%20contain%20itself%20from%20projecting%20this%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cswift%20counter-terrorist%20operation%20by%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%9D%20that%20had%20inflicted%20a%20setback%20to%20an%20alleged%20Pakistan%20plan%20for%20a%20new%20Khalistan%20project%20in%20India.%20%E2%80%9CNijjar%E2%80%99s%20killing%20proves%20that%20UK%2C%20Canada%2C%20Pakistan%20no%20longer%20safe%20havens%20for%20pro-Khalistani%20fugitives%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20publication%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theweek.in%2Fnews%2Fworld%2F2023%2F06%2F19%2Fkhalistan-tiger-force-chief-hardeep-singh-nijjar-shot-dead-in-canada.html%5C%22%3Eheadlined%20the%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20aftermath%20of%20Trudeau%E2%80%99s%20allegation%2C%20many%20pointed%20to%20Western%20double%20standards%20%E2%80%93%20they%20cause%20death%20and%20destruction%20in%20Afghanistan%20and%20Iraq%2C%20and%20we%20can%E2%80%99t%20take%20out%20our%20terrorists%20without%20being%20scolded%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFive%20Eyes%20vs%20%3Cem%3Eteesri%20aankh%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20Delhi%2C%20which%20wants%20to%20be%20seen%20rubbing%20shoulders%20at%20the%20high%20table%20with%20the%20G7%20even%20as%20it%20claims%20the%20leadership%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cglobal%20south%E2%80%9D%2C%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20allegation%20has%20created%20a%20dissonance%20in%20the%20post-G20%20narratives%20about%20India%2C%20its%20influence%20and%20clout%2C%20its%20convening%20power%2C%20and%20its%20bridging%20capabilities.%20All%20this%20because%20India%20has%20worked%20hard%20to%20project%20itself%20as%20a%20land%20of%201.5%20billion%20people%20that%20is%20not%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20thinks%20of%20itself%20as%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Western%20security%2Fintelligence%20alliance%2C%20and%20there%20has%20been%20talk%20that%20it%20should%20be%20inducted%20into%20the%20Five%20Eyes%20%E2%80%93%20the%20partnership%20between%20Australia%2C%20the%20US%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20Canada%20and%20New%20Zealand.%20But%20some%20of%20these%20security%20agencies%20have%20been%20wary%20for%20a%20while%20of%20their%20Indian%20counterparts%20even%20if%20the%20political%20leadership%20has%20gone%20all%20out%20to%20engage%20with%20the%20Modi%20government.%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20accusation%20is%20unlikely%20to%20increase%20confidence%20levels.%20For%20reasons%20not%20clear%2C%20the%20R%26amp%3BAW%20station%20chief%E2%80%99s%20post%20in%20Washington%20DC%2C%20which%20fell%20vacant%20a%20few%20months%20ago%2C%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20filled%20as%20the%20host%20government%20is%20yet%20to%20agree%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20nomination.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20wants%20the%20global%20spotlight%20on%20itself%2C%20but%20that%20brings%20more%20scrutiny%2C%20sets%20a%20higher%20bar.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fcanadas-allegations-will-bring-unwanted-attention-on-indian-immigrants-abroad%5C%22%3ECanada%E2%80%99s%20Allegations%20Will%20Bring%20Unwanted%20Attention%20on%20Indian%20Immigrants%20Abroad%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENot%20the%20first%20accusation%20of%20%E2%80%9Cinterference%E2%80%9D%20by%20Canada%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECanada%E2%80%99s%20own%20problems%20with%20RAW%20go%20back%20decades.%20But%20as%20recently%20as%202018%2C%20in%20a%20federal%20court%20in%20Canada%2C%20India%20was%20accused%20of%20%E2%80%9Cinterference%E2%80%9D%20in%20that%20country%E2%80%99s%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECanadian%20media%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobalnews.ca%2Fnews%2F6823170%2Fcanadian-politicians-targeted-indian-intelligence%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20R%26amp%3BAW%20and%20the%20Intelligence%20Bureau%20(IB)%20had%20attempted%20to%20use%20money%20and%20disinformation%20through%20an%20Indian%20citizen%3Cb%3E%20%3C%2Fb%3Eto%20%E2%80%9Ccovertly%20influence%E2%80%9D%20Canadian%20politicians%20to%20support%20Indian%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%20came%20to%20light%20when%20the%20Indian%20citizen%2C%20a%20journalist%2C%20identified%20only%20as%20AB%20and%20%E2%80%9Ceditor-in-chief%E2%80%9D%20in%20court%20documents%2C%20was%20accused%20of%20acting%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20two%20Indian%20intelligence%20agencies.%20He%20had%20applied%20to%20emigrate%20to%20Canada%20%E2%80%93%20his%20wife%20and%20daughter%20were%20already%20Canadian%20citizens%20at%20the%20time%20%E2%80%93%20and%20his%20role%20as%20a%20paid%20influencer%20of%20R%26amp%3BAW%20and%20the%20IB%20came%20up%20during%20checks%20on%20his%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20application%20was%20turned%20down%2C%20but%20a%20Canadian%20federal%20court%20overturned%20the%20charges%20against%20him%20and%20allowed%20him%20to%20stay%20but%20not%20before%20he%20was%20questioned%20threadbare%20by%20the%20court%20about%20his%20links%20to%20Indian%20intelligence%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20perhaps%20the%20first%20%E2%80%9Cpublicly%E2%80%9D%20alleged%20instance%20of%20clandestine%20foreign%20influence%20targeting%20Canadian%20politicians.%20Delhi%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20the%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHistory%20of%20bad%20blood%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201980s%2C%20the%20Royal%20Canadian%20Mounted%20Police%2C%20a%20law-enforcing%20agency%2C%20also%20performed%20the%20main%20intelligence%20role.%20As%20allegations%20of%20human%20rights%20violations%20mounted%20against%20what%20was%20principally%20a%20police%20organisation%2C%20it%20was%20decided%20to%20set%20up%20the%20Canadian%20Security%20Intelligence%20Service%20(CSIS).%20The%20CSIS%20came%20into%20existence%20in%201984%2C%20just%20a%20year%20before%20the%20Kanishka%20bombing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20the%20circumstances%20in%20which%20it%20was%20created%20and%20the%20botched%20investigation%20into%20the%20Kanishka%20bombing%2C%20CSIS%20and%20R%26amp%3BAW%20fell%20out%20quickly.%20The%20presence%20of%20a%20large%20Sikh%20diaspora%20in%20Canada%2C%20and%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20rights-based%20approach%20to%20the%20Khalistani%20activists%20among%20them%2C%20has%20been%20a%20major%20irritant%20in%20ties%2C%20surfacing%20every%20now%20and%20then%20over%20the%20last%20few%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2F03142916%2FScreen-Shot-2021-06-03-at-2.27.19-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221201%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2F03142916%2FScreen-Shot-2021-06-03-at-2.27.19-PM.png%201201w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2F03142916%2FScreen-Shot-2021-06-03-at-2.27.19-PM-300x114.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2F03142916%2FScreen-Shot-2021-06-03-at-2.27.19-PM-1024x391.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-532477%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22458%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ER%26amp%3BAW%E2%80%99s%20logo.%20Illustration%3A%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECSIS%20redlines%2C%20R%26amp%3BAW%20withdraws%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20too%20well%20known%20that%20at%20the%20time%2C%20the%20CSIS%20wanted%20R%26amp%3BAW%20to%20sign%20off%20on%20a%20MoU%20listing%20do%E2%80%99s%20and%20don%E2%80%99ts%20for%20foreign%20intelligence%20operatives%2C%20which%20the%20Indian%20agency%20refused%20to%20do.%20Over%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20R%26amp%3BAW%20and%20IB%20did%20not%20post%20anyone%20in%20Canada.%20A%20semblance%20of%20Indian%20intelligence%20presence%20in%20Canada%20was%20maintained%20through%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Security%20in%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%2C%20manned%20mainly%20by%20police%20officers.%20These%20officials%20are%20posted%20to%20missions%20abroad%20to%20manage%20the%20security%20of%20the%20diplomats.%C2%A0In%20Canada%2C%20in%20a%20decade%20crucial%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20battle%20to%20save%20Punjab%2C%20they%20were%20tasked%20with%20part-time%20intelligence%20work%20too.%20This%20continued%20until%20matters%20were%20resolved%20in%20the%20mid-1990s%2C%20but%20the%20larger%20relationship%20was%20always%20a%20case%20of%20one%20step%20forward%2C%20two%20steps%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAnother%20G20%20summit%2C%20another%20row%20and%20an%20apology%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202010%2C%20Canada%20was%20the%20host%20of%20the%20G-20%20summit.%20A%20month%20before%20the%20event%2C%20which%20was%20to%20be%20held%20in%20Toronto%2C%20a%20massive%20row%20erupted%20over%20refusal%20of%20visas%20to%20former%20intelligence%20and%20former%20Army%20officials%20who%20apparently%20wanted%20to%20visit%20their%20family%20members%20in%20that%20country.%20The%20Canadian%20High%20Commission%20in%20Delhi%20rejected%20the%20visa%20of%20S.S.%20Sidhu%2C%20a%20retired%20IB%20official.%20Lt%20Gen%20(retd)%20A.S.%20Bahia%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Armed%20Forces%20Tribunal%20in%20Chandigarh%2C%20was%20also%20refused%20a%20visa%20in%20May%20of%20the%20same%20year.%20After%20BSF%20jawan%20Fateh%20Singh%20Pandher%2C%20who%20had%20his%20visa%20application%20rejected%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20he%20had%20been%20associated%20with%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnotoriously%20violent%E2%80%9D%20force%2C%20went%20to%20town%20with%20the%20denial%2C%20several%20Army%20and%20paramilitary%20officers%20came%20out%20too%20with%20their%20own%20rejections.%20The%20reasons%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fcanada-asked-to-set-record-straight%2Farticleshow%2F5983324.cms%3Futm_source%3Dcontentofinterest%26utm_medium%3Dtext%26utm_campaign%3Dcppst%5C%22%3Eranged%20from%3C%2Fa%3E%20apprehension%20that%20the%20person%20would%20engage%20in%20espionage%2C%20or%20violent%20activities%2C%20to%20causing%20harm%20to%20Canadian%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20emerged%20that%20a%20serving%20IB%20officer%2C%20in%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20security%20liaison%20office%2C%20who%20was%20deputed%20to%20travel%20with%20him%20to%20Toronto%2C%20had%20also%20been%20denied%20a%20visa%20%E2%80%93%20but%20was%20given%20one%20after%20the%20government%20stepped%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20public%20outrage%20grew%20and%20the%20BJP%20stepped%20up%20attacks%20on%20the%20government%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cweak%E2%80%9D%20foreign%20policy%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20summoned%20the%20Canadian%20high%20commissioner%20in%20Delhi%20Joseph%20Caron%20twice%20%E2%80%93%20just%20like%20the%20current%20envoy%20Cameron%20McKay%20was%20earlier%20this%20week.%20According%20to%20then%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.M.%20Krishna%2C%20the%20message%20was%20conveyed%20that%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20remarks%20against%20Indian%20security%20services%20were%20%E2%80%9Cunacceptable%E2%80%9D.%20Canada%20made%20a%20public%20apology.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EBJP-Khalistan%20backchannel%20talks%3F%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20columnist%20in%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ENational%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20newspaper%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnationalpost.com%2Fopinion%2Fterry-glavin-after-trudeau-alleges-murder-plot-canada-india-relations-may-be-irreparable%5C%22%3Ehas%20pointed%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccovert%20operation%2C%20a%20backchannel%20reconciliation%20effort%20between%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20and%20veteran%20Khalistanis%E2%80%9D%20who%20were%20wearying%20of%20their%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETerry%20Glavin%2C%20the%20columnist%2C%20is%20a%20well-known%20figure%20in%20Canadian%20journalism.%20In%20the%20column%2C%20in%20which%20he%20lights%20into%20Trudeau%20for%20%E2%80%9Cirreparably%E2%80%9D%20damaging%20ties%20with%20India%20and%20handing%20Beijing%20a%20victory%2C%20Glavin%20suggests%20that%20the%20BJP%20was%20in%20touch%20with%20Ripudaman%20Malik%2C%20one%20of%20three%20main%20accused%20in%20the%20Kanishka%20bombing%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMalik%20had%20been%20acquitted%20by%20the%20courts%2C%20and%20in%20January%202022%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fcanadian-sikh-ripudaman-singh-malik-enigma-killing-mystery%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20letter%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20thanking%20him%20for%20removing%20names%20of%20some%20Sikhs%20abroad%20from%20a%20list%20that%20barred%20them%20from%20entering%20India.%20He%20also%20wrote%20that%20anti-India%20elements%20in%20the%20Sikh%20community%20were%20orchestrating%20a%20campaign%20against%20the%20Indian%20prime%20minister.%20There%20was%20a%20backlash%20against%20him%20in%20Surrey%2C%20where%20he%20had%20become%20a%20successful%20businessman.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Glavin%2C%20his%20murder%20%E2%80%9Cpoints%20directly%20to%20the%20BJP-Khalistani%20peace%20talks%E2%80%9D%2C%20quoting%20a%20UK-based%20Sikh%2C%20who%20he%20describes%20as%20a%20backchannel%20mediator%20to%20support%20his%20theory%20that%20Trudeau%20bowed%20to%20the%20Khalistani%20lobby%20to%20sabotage%20the%20talks.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20Indian%20media%20reports%20quoted%20unnamed%20Indian%20intelligence%20sources%20suggesting%20that%20Malik%20had%20been%20eliminated%20by%20Nijjar%2C%20with%20whom%20he%20had%20crossed%20swords%20over%20control%20of%20a%20gurudwara%20in%20Surrey.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGlavin%E2%80%99s%20speculation%20about%20the%20BJP-Khalistani%20backchannel%20could%20not%20be%20confirmed%20independently%2C%20but%20it%20suggests%20that%20relations%20between%20the%20security%20agencies%20of%20the%20two%20countries%20have%20been%20far%20worse%20than%20they%20have%20seemed%20for%20quite%20a%20while.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20tit-for-tat%20explusions%20of%20the%20RAW%20station%20chief%20at%20the%20Indian%20mission%20in%20Ottawa%20and%20the%20CSIS%20head%20in%20the%20Canadian%20mission%20in%20Delhi%20hark%20back%20to%20the%201980s%20when%20Indian%20intelligence%20officials%20were%20hounded%20and%20exposed%20in%20cities%20like%20Vancouver%20and%20Toronto.%20India%20may%20be%20the%20bigger%20loser%20in%20this%20revenge%20game%20because%20of%20the%20asymmetry%20in%20their%20respective%20priorities%3A%20it%20is%20not%20as%20important%20for%20CSIS%20to%20maintain%20a%20presence%20in%20India%2C%20as%20it%20is%20for%20RAW%20to%20be%20in%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695298524000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F21173817%2F1024px-The_Prime_Minister_Shri_Narendra_Modi_with_the_Prime_Minister_of_Canada_Mr._Justin_Trudeau_at_Hyderabad_House_in_New_Delhi_on_February_23_2018_1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-canada-nijjar-modi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Delhi%20wants%20to%20be%20seen%20rubbing%20shoulders%20at%20the%20high%20table%20with%20the%20G7%20even%20as%20it%20claims%20the%20leadership%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cglobal%20south%E2%80%9D.%20Greater%20influence%20brings%20a%20higher%20bar%20and%20more%20scrutiny.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A23%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-canada-nijjar-modi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Best%20pictures%20from%20state%20visit%20to%20France%20-%20as%20Queen%20plays%20table%20te