t's%20Perceived%20Crackdown%20on%20Dissent%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F14000534%2F1600px-Prime_Minister_of_India_Narendra_Modi_at_an_informal_meeting_of_heads_of_state_and_government_of_the_BRICS_countries_Hamburg_2017.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Two%20analysis%20pieces%20and%20an%20editorial%20in%20three%20foreign%20publications%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Atlantic%2C%20The%20Economist%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%3Cem%3E%20The%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20have%20connected%20allegations%20levelled%20by%20Canada%20over%20India%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20the%20murder%20of%20a%20Sikh%20activist%20to%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20strongman%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20three%20have%20mentioned%20increasing%20global%20perception%20of%20Modi%20as%20a%20figure%20who%20cracks%20down%20on%20dissenters%20and%20the%20press.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98The%20Killing%20in%20Canada%20Shows%20What%20India%20Has%20Become%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EAtlantic%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Finternational%2Farchive%2F2023%2F09%2Fcanada-nijjar-killing-india-trudeau-sikh%2F675383%2F%5C%22%3Enoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20its%20analysis%20this%20shifting%20perception%20of%20the%20Modi%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Indian%20government%20has%20denied%20involvement%20in%20the%20killing%2C%20but%20under%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20it%20has%20become%20illiberal%20at%20home%20and%20bellicose%20abroad%2C%20such%20that%20assassinations%20on%20foreign%20soil%20are%20no%20longer%20an%20unimaginable%20part%20of%20its%20agenda%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%3A%20%E2%80%9CNew%20Delhi%2C%20in%20other%20words%2C%20could%20well%20be%20a%20government%20that%20will%20do%20anything%20to%20silence%20dissidents.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20article%20traces%20the%20Khalistani%20movement%2C%20including%20the%20bombing%20of%20the%20Air%20India%20flight%20in%201985%20and%20the%20assassination%20of%20late%20prime%20minister%20Indira%20Gandhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20article%20says%20that%20Nijjar%E2%80%99s%20activism%20was%20peaceful%20and%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20alleged%20terror%20activities%20of%20those%20who%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20India%20is%20behind%20Nijjar%E2%80%99s%20killing%2C%20its%20actions%20don%E2%80%99t%20reflect%20fears%20of%20Sikh%20secession%20so%20much%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20transformation%20into%20an%20illiberal%20state%20where%20the%20government%20has%20elevated%20one%20religion%20%E2%80%93%20Hinduism%20%E2%80%93%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20all%20others%2C%20and%20where%20policy%20makers%20tolerate%20little%20dissent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20article%20claims%20that%20so%20far%20Sikhs%20have%20been%20%E2%80%9Cspared%20the%20worst%20ethnonationalist%20measures%2C%E2%80%9D%20compared%20to%20Muslims%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20but%20that%20they%20are%20%E2%80%9Cno%20longer%20as%20exempt%E2%80%9D%20after%20this%20week%E2%80%99s%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20reason%2C%20the%20article%20cites%20Sikh%20farmers%E2%80%99%20roles%20in%20the%20historic%20protests%20that%20led%20to%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20the%20farm%20laws%20by%20the%20Modi%20government%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20article%20also%20observes%20why%20United%20States%E2%80%99%20claim%20that%20India%20is%20its%20natural%20friend%20might%20not%20be%20true%20if%20the%20latter%20is%20%E2%80%9Ctrying%20to%20create%20not%20a%20great%2C%20peaceful%20democracy%20but%20an%20avowedly%20Hindu%20power%20that%20dominates%20South%20Asia.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98If%20India%20ordered%20a%20murder%20in%20Canada%2C%20there%20must%20be%20consequences%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EEconomist%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Fleaders%2F2023%2F09%2F20%2Fif-india-ordered-a-murder-in-canada-there-must-be-consequences%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20India%20has%20%E2%80%9Clong%20been%20accused%20of%20assassinating%20militants%20and%20dissidents%20in%20its%20own%20messy%20region%3B%20never%20previously%20in%20the%20friendly%20and%20orderly%20West.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENoting%20the%20present%20imbroglio%2C%20the%20magazine%20noted%2C%20similar%20to%C2%A0%3Cem%3EAtlantic%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20America%20and%20its%20allies%20should%20consider%20this%20a%20warning%20shot%20against%20their%20own%20eager%20to%20overlook%20the%20%E2%80%9Ctoo%20frequent%20abuses%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Modi%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESimilar%20to%20the%20above%20analysis%2C%20the%20outlet%20traces%20the%20alleged%20killing%20as%20an%20extension%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20crackdown%20against%20dissenters.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COn%20its%20own%20turf%20it%20has%20muzzled%20the%20press%2C%20cowed%20the%20courts%20and%20persecuted%20minorities%2C%20even%20though%20none%20is%20a%20threat%20to%20it.%20The%20alleged%20assassination%20in%20Canada%2C%20too%2C%20appears%20gratuitous%20as%20well%20as%20wrong.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20making%20of%20martyrs%20out%20of%20separatist%20leaders%20is%20ultimately%20a%20gift%20to%20their%20beleaguered%20cause%2C%20the%20piece%20notes.%20This%20causal%20feeling%20of%20insecurity%20in%20India%20is%20a%20feature%20of%20its%20rapid%20rise%2C%20%3Cem%3EEconomist%3C%2Fem%3E%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20country%20is%20almost%20invariably%20weaker%20than%20its%20leaders%20publicly%20proclaim%2C%20yet%20stronger%20than%20they%20privately%20fear%E2%80%94and%20that%20mismatch%20is%20a%20recipe%20for%20miscalculations%20of%20this%20kind.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20piece%20also%20says%20that%20the%20West%E2%80%99s%20claim%20of%20shared%20values%20opens%20them%20to%20charges%20of%20hypocrisy.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20investigation%20confirms%20Indian%20involvement%20in%20this%20crime%2C%20it%20is%20time%20for%20a%20tougher%20line%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Times%20view%20on%20the%20killing%20of%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%3A%20Prime%20Suspect%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thetimes.co.uk%2Farticle%2Fthe-times-view-on-the-killing-of-hardeep-singh-nijjar-prime-suspect-5kqzts80r%5C%22%3Enoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20if%20the%20allegation%20of%20Canada%20%E2%80%93%20a%20nation%20called%20%E2%80%9Costensibly%20friendly%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20paper%20%E2%80%93%20is%20true%20then%20it%20could%20mark%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20how%20India%20is%20perceived%20internationally.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMr%20Modi%2C%20a%20substantial%20figure%20in%20global%20politics%2C%20could%20find%20himself%20cast%20alongside%20Vladimir%20Putin%20as%20a%20rogue%20actor%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20editorial%20too%20notes%20how%20under%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cmuscular%20instincts%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0India%20has%20slipped%20down%20global%20rankings%20for%20religious%20and%20press%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20editorial%20cites%20the%20BBC%20office%20raids%20following%20the%20documentary%20on%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20the%20Gujarat%20riots.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDespite%20fears%20about%20his%20growing%20authoritarianism%20Mr%20Modi%20has%20maintained%20his%20position%20in%20the%20global%20mainstream.%20But%20killing%20Mr%20Nijjar%2C%20who%20was%20designated%20by%20Delhi%20as%20a%20terrorist%20for%20his%20championing%20of%20a%20Sikh%20homeland%20in%20the%20Punjab%2C%20takes%20India%20out%20of%20that%20mainstream%20and%20into%20the%20dubious%20company%20of%20%E2%80%9Chit%20job%E2%80%9D%20states%20like%20Russia.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20serious%20headache%20for%20the%20British%2C%20who%20are%20caught%20between%20two%20powerful%20Commonwealth%20members%2C%20this%20editorial%20says%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20diplomatic%20fallout%20from%20this%20affair%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20extensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695287135000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F14000534%2F1600px-Prime_Minister_of_India_Narendra_Modi_at_an_informal_meeting_of_heads_of_state_and_government_of_the_BRICS_countries_Hamburg_2017.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fcanada-india-nijjar-killing-modi-government%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'The%20Indian%20government%20has%20denied%20involvement%20in%20the%20killing%2C%20but%20under%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20it%20has%20become%20illiberal%20at%20home%20and%20bellicose%20abroad%2C%20such%20that%20assassinations%20on%20foreign%20soil%20are%20no%20longer%20an%20unimaginable%20part%20of%20its%20agenda.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A38%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fcanada-india-nijjar-killing-modi-government%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Parliament%20Security%20Staff's%20New%20Uniform%20Withdrawn%20Following%20Complaints%20Over%20Fabric%2C%20Design%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123153%2Fimage3-1.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20new%20uniform%20introduced%20for%20the%20parliament%20security%20staff%20was%20withdrawn%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20September%2020%2C%20just%20a%20day%20after%20the%20staff%20started%20wearing%20it.%20There%20have%20been%20several%20complaints%20from%20the%20security%20staff%20stating%20that%20they%20were%20sweating%20profusely%20due%20to%20the%20fabric%20used%20and%20the%20design%20of%20the%20new%20outfit.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20500-odd%20parliament%20security%20staff%20turned%20up%20to%20work%20on%20Wednesday%20in%20their%20usual%20navy