7B%22title%22%3A%22Bangladesh%20PM%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20Daughter%20Up%20Against%20Nepal's%20Nominee%20in%20WHO%20Regional%20Election%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F21133713%2FF5guFiCXcAACIIW.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhen%20Bangladesh%20Prime%20Minister%20Sheikh%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20daughter%20Saima%20Wazed%20accompanied%20her%20mother%20to%20the%20G20%20Summit%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20observers%20were%20not%20surprised.%20Wazed%20is%20contesting%20elections%20to%20become%20regional%20director%20of%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation%20(WHO)%2C%20and%20is%20looking%20to%20get%20India%E2%80%99s%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWazed%20has%20a%20masters%20degree%20in%20psychology%20and%20specialises%20in%20autism.%20Her%20official%20title%20is%20chairperson%20of%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20National%20Advisory%20Committee%20on%20Autism%20and%20Neurodevelopmental%20Disorders.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20candidate%20she%20is%20up%20against%2C%20though%20%E2%80%93%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20Shambhu%20Prasad%20Acharya%2C%20one%20of%20the%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20senior-most%20officials%20%E2%80%93%20may%20also%20be%20expecting%20India%E2%80%99s%20vote%2C%20given%20the%20close%20ties%20between%20the%20two%20neighbouring%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20matters%20who%20becomes%20their%20regional%20directors%20because%20they%20have%20considerable%20decentralised%20authority%20to%20influence%20the%20health%20chances%20of%20billions%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhealthpolicy-watch.news%2Fshenanigans-in-who-south-east-asia-as-politicians-daughter-contests-for-election-as-regional-director%2F%5C%22%3EHealth%20Policy%20Watch%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EElections%20to%20appoint%20the%20WHO%20South%20East%20Asia%20Regional%20Office%20(SEARO)%20director%20will%20be%20held%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20where%20SEARO%20is%20based%2C%20between%20Oct