0History%5D%20have%20been%20soul%20food%20to%20someone%20at%20some%20point%20in%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20points%20out.%20For%20Tanya%2C%20her%20own%20fondest%20memories%20involve%20her%20%3Cem%3Eammama%20%3C%2Fem%3E(grandmother).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20book%2C%20she%20recalls%20how%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20starch%20white%20%3Cem%3Echatta%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%3Cem%3E%20mundu%20%3C%2Fem%3E(traditional%20attire%20worn%20by%20catholic%20women%20in%20Kerala)%20yellowed%20through%20the%20day%20as%20%3Cem%3Emasalas%3C%2Fem%3E%20stained%20it.%20Long%20hours%20of%20working%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3Ekushinchya%3C%2Fem%3E%20(kitchen)%20to%20serve%20a%20large%20joint%20family%20of%2030%20were%20to%20blame.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20all%20was%20forgotten%20as%20the%20guests%20relished%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F329667%2Fpalghar-kiran-kamdar-free-homemade-khichdi-for-patients-hospital-parkinson-disease%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehomemade%20rose%20cookies%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20devoured%20the%20%3Cem%3Emeen%20pollichathu%3C%2Fem%3E%20(fish%20cooked%20in%20banana%20leaves)%20dish.%20These%20frequent%20visitors%20were%20not%20always%20relatives%2C%20but%20a%20host%20of%20businessmen%2C%20political%20people%2C%20nationalists%2C%20and%20missionaries%2C%20all%20part%20of%20the%20Independence%20movement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFood%2C%20she%20discovered%2C%20was%20always%20the%20soul%20of%20the%20home.%20And%20still%20is.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20her%20%3Cem%3Eammama%3C%2Fem%3E%20passed%20away%20at%20the%20ripe%20old%20age%20of%20104%2C%20to%20Tanya%20it%20felt%20almost%20like%20a%20storehouse%20of%20culinary%20delights%20went%20away%20with%20her.%20It%20made%20her%20think%20of%20all%20the%20women%20who%2C%20like%20her%20grandmother%2C%20had%20brewed%20magic%20through%20their%20recipes.%20These%20would%20be%20lost%20in%20time%20if%20not%20preserved.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFuelled%20