ries%20from%20Spain%20and%20Portugal%2C%20bringing%20their%20food%20along%20with%20them.%20In%20the%20book%2C%20Tanya%20writes%20that%20it%20was%20due%20to%20the%20Portuguese%20tyranny%20that%20they%20fled%20to%20Kochi%20and%20thrived%20in%20Jew%20Town%20in%20Mattancherry.%20While%20today%2C%20only%20vestiges%20of%20the%20Malabari%20synagogues%20are%20present%20in%20Kerala%2C%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F319669%2Fbengaluru-family-starts-traditional-south-indian-food-stall-business-in-brooklyn-swetha-raju%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20the%20culinary%20legacy%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethey%20left%20behind%20is%20still%20prevalent.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Eispethi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(red%20beef%20stew)%20and%20%3Cem%3Eneiappam%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20breakfast%20or%20tea%20time%20snack%2C%20which%20the%20Jews%20especially%20prepare%20during%20Hannukah%20as%20a%20popular%20treat%20during%20the%20festival%2C%20%3Cem%3Eneiappam%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20popular%20across%20Kerala%20and%20also%20called%20%3Cem%3Eunniyappam%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20book%20mentions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694844000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FScreenshot_20230915-172153_Kindle-1694787839.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D330111%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22All%20the%20'ammammas'%20of%20Kerala%20have%20reached%20into%20their%20treasure%20trove%20of%20recipes%20to%20dig%20out%20the%20most%20precious%20ones%20which%20have%20made%20it%20to%20Tanya%20Abraham's%20book%2C%20'Eating%20with%20History'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Krystelle%20Dsouza%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F330111%2Ftanya-abraham-journalist-writes-eating-with-history-kerala-food-recipes-history%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meet%20the%20Kerala%20Doctor%20Who%20Helped%20Detect%20Nipah%20Outbreak%20Early%2C%20This%20Time%20%26amp%3B%20In%202018%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EOn%2010%20September%202023%2C%20four%20people%20were%20admitted%20to%20Aster%20MIMS%20Hospital%20in%20Kozhikode%2C%20Kerala.%20This%20included%20three%20children%20and%20one%20adult%2C%20all%20of%20whom%20were%20related%20to%20each%20other.%20They%20all%20presented%20with%20fever%2C%20cough%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F220706%2Fcoronavirus-india-covid19-kerala-ias-hero-doctor-rajeev-sadanandan-nipah-india-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erespiratory%20symptoms%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20further%20enquiry%2C%20the%20multidisciplinary%20team%20of%20doctors%20treating%20them%20found%20out%20that%20there%20was%20a%20death%20in%20their%20family%2010%20days%20back.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20father%20of%20two%20of%20the%20children%2C%20a%2049-year-old%2C%20had%20died%20in%20another%20hospital%20nearby.%20Interestingly%2C%20all%20patients%20hailed%20from%20Maruthonkara%2C%20which%20was%20near%20the%20epicentre%20of%20the%20Nipah%20virus%20outbreak%20in%20Kerala%20in%202018.%20This%20worried%20the%20treating%20team%2C%20which%20included%20Dr%20Anoop%20Kumar%20AS%20who%20is%20the%20director%20of%20North%20Kerala%20(Cluster)%20of%20Critical%20Care%20Medicine%20at%20the%20Aster%20Hospitals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENipah%20is%20a%20zoonotic%20virus%20that%20spreads%20from%20infected%20animals%20like%20bats%20or%20pigs%20to%20humans.%20Dr%20Kumar%20has%20also%20been%20credited%20for%20catching%20the%20first%20Nipah%20outbreak%20in%202018%20in%20time.%20His%20quick%20thinking%20and%20swift%20action%20helped%20the%20patients%20back%20then%20and%20are%20showing%20the%20same%20effect%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20clustering%20of%20cases%20with%20respiratory%20symptoms%2C%20coupled%20with%20a%20probable%20index%20(primary)%20case%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20hail%20from%20the%20area%20near%20the%20previous%20epicentre%2C%20gave%20us%20a%20suspicion%20that%20it%20was%20a%20rare%20virus%20and%20that%20it%20could%20be%20Nipah%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dr%20Kumar%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20of%20doctors%20acted%20quickly%20by%20isolating%20these%20four%20patients%20and%20sent%20their%20samples%20to%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Virology%20(NIV)%2C%20Pune.%20They%20also%20informed%20the%20state%20health%20authorities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20sudden%20death%20on%2011%20September%20of%20a%2042-year-old%20patient%20with%20similar%20symptoms%20but%20in%20a%20different%20hospital%20kept%20the%20doctors%20suspicious.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETracing%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%3Cstrong%3E%20disease%20route%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20837px)%20100vw%2C%20837px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fdr-anoop-kumar-as-1694787970.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22837%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr%20Anoop%20Kumar%20AS%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fdr-anoop-kumar-as-1694787970.jpeg%20837w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fdr-anoop-kumar-as-1694787970-241x300.jpeg%20241w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fdr-anoop-kumar-as-1694787970-500x623.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fdr-anoop-kumar-as-1694787970-768x957.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fdr-anoop-kumar-as-1694787970-150x187.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-330118%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221043%5C%22%3E%